subSubSection.paragraph:
Members of the Alicellidae are all deep-sea scavengers and the highly modified mandibles appear to be an important modification to this mode of life. Alicellids may be associated with thermal vents (
Barnard & Ingram 1990
) or living on the deep abyssal and hadal plains where species such as
Alicella gigantea
are among the deepest living and largest amphipods known (
Chevreux 1899
;
Barnard & Ingram 1986
;
De Broyer & Thurston 1987
).
